GateDocument.TextWithNodes: # # # CALL FOR PAPERS # # # International Workshop on New Database Technologies for Collaborative Work Support and Spatio- Temporal Data Management ( NewDB'98 ) Singapore , Nov . 19 - 20 , 1998 In conjunction with the 17 th International Conference on Conceptual Modeling ( ER'98 ) Singapore , Nov . 16 - 19 , 1998 http : / / www . iscs . nus . edu . sg / ~ er 98 Aim : Support of collaborative work and management of spatio-temporal data has become one of the most interesting and important database applications , which is due to the tremendous progress of database and its surrounding technologies in the last decade . This workshop aims to bring together researchers , developers , and practitioners from academia and industry , and to serve as a forum for discussion , presentation , and exchange of the newest technologies andideas in this field . Papers describing prototype systems are especially welcome . Suggested Topics ( but not limited to ) : Collaborative virtual environment , spatio-temporal databases , VRML databases , moving objects , spatio-temporal multimedia databases , spatio-temporal indexing , geographic information systems Submission and Publication Details : Authors are invited to submit research contributions representing original , previously unpublished work . Submitted papers will be carefully reviewed by three members of the program committee based on originality , significance , technical soundness , and clarity of exposition . The workshop proceedings will be published as a volume of Advanced Database Research and Development Series from World- Scientific . Also , selected papers will be published in the Transactions on Databases of the Information Processing Society of Japan ( IPSJ ) . For submission , please send four hard copies to the program committee chair . IMPORTANT DATES : * Submission of abstracts : August 9 , 1998 * Submission of full papers : August 16 , 1998 * Notification of acceptance : October 1 , 1998 * Camera-ready copies due : October 22 , 1998 The authors are requested to send the abstract of the paper including the paper title , keywords , author names , addresses , and affiliations , by email to masunaga @ mysm . mb . euq .
